THE National Commissioner of the South African Police
Service (SAPS) General Khehla Sitole and Minister of Police, Minister Bheki
Cele handed over 53 new high performance cars to the Gauteng Flying Squared. This happened as they launched the SAPS Anti-Corruption Strategy in Pretoria on Thursday. Police spokesperson Colonel Athlenda Mathe said this is in an effort to combat
fraud and corruption within its ranks. “The launch of the strategy coincides with Africa Public
Service Month, which is annually celebrated in the month of June. The reason for the integration is that the theme for Public
Service Month’s celebrations 2018 is “Winning the fight against Corruption,” Mathe
said. 